<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-390-156  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 390 156.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  June 1990 v7 n6 p201(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CD Companion Series: Ludwig van Beethoven Symphony No. 9.andO;(Software Review) (combination HyperCard and audio CD program)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Weiman, Liza.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Voyager Company's $99.95 CD Companion Series: Ludwig VanBeethoven Symphony No.andP;  9 is a highly interactive combinationHyperCard and CD-ROM audio program designed for teaching musicappreciation.andP;  It uses a five-level HyperCard stack to control aCD player and a digitally remastered 1966 Decca recording ofBeethoven's Ninth Symphony.andP;  The program provides a 'guided tour'through the music; users can switch from one level to another forin-depth exploration or return to the symphony for uninterruptedlistening.andP;  The 'Pocket Guide' level presents the symphonystructurally.andP;  Above it are Beethoven's World and the Art ofListening, which provide background information and explanationsof the symphonic form as applied to the Ninth Symphony.andP;  The'Close Reading' level provides commentary on the symphony as itplays, and the 'Ninth Game' is an irreverent 'quiz' mode designedfor one to four players.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Voyager Co. (products).andO;Product:   Hypercard (Data base management system) (usage)CD Companion Series: Ludwig van Beethoven Symphony No. 9.andO;(Computer program).andO;Topic:     CD-ROMMultimedia SoftwareSoftware packagesEducational SoftwareInteractive Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>